race.comment: TIKKEN (5) is fitter for three runs back and looks close to a win. Little below best last time but placed 2/2 this journey and best figures stack right up this level. ROYAL INFANTRY (9) resumed with a second at Avoca and that figure was just off his career best. Fitter again and expected to go close. CALUSA'S FURY (1) is a lightly raced galloper who actually raced in a maiden here last year and finished runner-up. Fitter for three runs since a long break and can go one better this time around. KISS'N DANCE (3) has obviously had issues and returns after a long break. Fitter for two trials and off the inside drawn for a soft run. SARAYA (8) raced on speed last time and was solid enough. Has the claim and will take catching.
